Usernames can be very tided to the project/site, that was the reason behind the (now deprecated) ``SOCIAL_AUTH_USERNAME_FIXER``.

The preferred method now is defining a pipeline entry similar to this one:

    def clean_username(*args, **kwargs):
        if 'username' in kwargs:
            return { 'username': re.sub('[^a-zA-Z_0-9]', '', kwargs['username']) }

and put it right after ``'social_auth.backends.pipeline.user.get_username',`` entry in the pipeline.

Check the pipeline doc for details at http://django-social-auth.readthedocs.org/en/latest/pipeline.html

